                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 17554/22.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires at Lima</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-03-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 11, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your March 7. This Department would sincerely deplore haste or severance of
                    diplomatic relations between Chile and Peru on account of dispute over status of
                    priests at Tacna. Department believes that at present the giving of instructions
                    to our Chargé d’Affaires at Santiago to take charge of Peruvian Legation would
                    be premature.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
